						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the central shrine in the Siddhanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarmaṉ Rājēndra Year 3.</hi></p>						

						<p>This epigraph in the absence of a <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king may be assigned to Rājēndra I of accession 1012 A.D. on the basis of palaeography. Palaeographically, the record may be assigned to about the first quarter of the eleventh century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of [12] sheep for a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the deity Kaṅkāḷadēva in the temple of Siddhēśvara by a lady named Ādaṉ-aḍiyāḷ, wife of Nallāṉaḍigaḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tanichchēvagappornāyaṉ, a <hi rend="italic">vellāḷa</hi> of Tirunaṟaiyūr a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Tirunaṟaiyūr-nāḍu in Kshatriyaśikhāmaṇivaḷanāḍu. A shepherd <hi rend="italic">(maṉṟāḍi)</hi> Sāttaṉ-bhaṭṭaṉ undertook the gift and he was to supply annually 12 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of ghee measured by <hi rend="italic">Siddaṉ</hi> at the rate of one <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> per month and <hi rend="italic">araippiḍi</hi> daily to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
